01:06:17.620 --> 01:06:19.040
But right now we've got some more important.

01:06:19.060 --> 01:06:25.300
So you could sort of like sort not just on time and other sorts of things for all sort of stuff.

01:06:25.420 --> 01:06:26.200
I think it would be beautiful.

01:06:26.560 --> 01:06:29.160
You know, a lot of ways you could add this in to places.

01:06:29.920 --> 01:06:35.940
Yeah, I mean, as far as customer service goes, the one thing I do hope is that at some point, I'm still always able to call a human if need be.

01:06:36.260 --> 01:06:42.040
Like, that's one concern I do have in that domain is that people are going to look at this as a cost center instead of a service center.

01:06:42.960 --> 01:06:47.400
Well, you know, once it becomes – the LLMs, people are trying, right?

01:06:47.520 --> 01:06:55.100
But there was – gosh, one of the car manufacturers, like their little chatbot completely lied about what they covered under the warranty.

01:06:56.160 --> 01:06:56.720
Oh, my gosh.

01:06:57.060 --> 01:06:59.160
But they got served because of that, didn't they?

01:06:59.280 --> 01:07:03.440
I remember that a judge had to look at it and said, well, your service has said that.

01:07:03.960 --> 01:07:04.220
Yeah, exactly.

01:07:04.480 --> 01:07:09.020
Yeah, I believe they had to live up to it, which is not great for them, but I also taught

01:07:09.040 --> 01:07:09.420
them a lesson.

